---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="fail2zig — VibeJam Spring '26 submission"
  description="A modern intrusion prevention system built in five days for VibeJam Spring '26. Single static binary, zero runtime dependencies, a real internet-exposed honeypot defending itself in real time."
>
  <div class="vibejam-wrap">
    <!-- hero · the contest ────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <section class="hero" aria-label="VibeJam Spring 2026">
      <figure class="hero-poster">
        <img
          src="/vibejam.webp"
          alt="VibeJam Spring '26 — For the Development of Serious Software"
          width="800"
          height="800"
          loading="eager"
          decoding="async"
        />
      </figure>

      <div class="hero-meta">
        <p class="hero-kicker">submission for</p>
        <h1 class="hero-title">VibeJam Spring '26</h1>
        <p class="hero-theme">For the Development of Serious Software</p>

        <dl class="hero-grid">
          <div>
            <dt>Dates</dt>
            <dd>Apr 20 <span class="sep">→</span> Apr 24, 2026</dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt>Duration</dt>
            <dd>5 days · 120 hours continuous</dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt>Prize pool</dt>
            <dd>$40,000+</dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt>Community</dt>
            <dd><a href="https://reddit.com/r/vibecoding" rel="noopener">r/vibecoding</a></dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt>Hosted by</dt>
            <dd>Marcus Estes</dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt>Sponsors</dt>
            <dd>VibesOS · Anything.com</dd>
          </div>
        </dl>

        <p class="hero-intro">
          <strong>fail2zig.</strong> A modern intrusion prevention system, built solo in five&nbsp;days.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- theme vs solution ────────────────────────────────── -->
    <section class="row row-story" aria-label="Theme and solution">
      <article class="card card-theme">
        <p class="card-label">Theme</p>
        <h2 class="card-head">Escape the Underclass</h2>
        <p>
          The security world quietly accepts a class of infrastructure risk as the cost of doing
          business: unbounded memory growth under sustained attack, CLI-coupled action chains that
          stack when the firewall is busy, general-purpose engines running in the hot path where
          specialized ones belong.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>fail2ban</strong> has protected the open internet for two decades. It's an impressive
          run, built on the technology of 2004: a Python runtime, a regex engine, a shell-out action model.
          Those were reasonable choices for their era, and the body of operator knowledge built on top
          of them is irreplaceable.
        </p>
        <p class="card-close">
          The underclass isn't fail2ban. It's the mindset that accepts 2004 as permanent.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="card card-solution">
        <p class="card-label">Solution</p>
        <h2 class="card-head">A serious runtime, in five days</h2>
        <p>fail2zig starts from the runtime up.</p>
        <p>
          The <code>jail.conf</code> format is the de facto standard for intrusion-prevention config.
          fail2zig reads it natively: the import pipeline parses the full <code>.conf</code> tree, translates
          Python regex patterns to specialized match functions, maps action names to native backends,
          and emits a validated TOML config. An existing fail2ban deployment migrates with one command,
          no rewrites.
        </p>
        <p class="card-close">
          What fail2zig contributes is the <strong>runtime underneath</strong>: one 877&nbsp;KB
          static musl binary with zero runtime dependencies, a comptime-specialized parser instead
          of a regex engine, netlink to the kernel for nftables, bounded memory under attack, and a
          live event feed for operators.
        </p>
      </article>
    </section>

    <p class="pull-under">Five days. One person. Escape from the underclass.</p>

    <!-- what shipped · tech stack ─────────────────────────────── -->
    <section class="row row-tables" aria-label="What shipped and tech stack">
      <div class="table-col">
        <div class="eyebrow"><span class="dot"></span>What shipped</div>
        <h2 class="table-head">Built in five days.</h2>
        <table class="stat-table">
          <tbody>
            <tr
              ><td class="cmp-leader">Lines of code</td><td
                >33,342 &middot; 18K Zig &middot; 15K web</td
              ></tr
            >
            <tr
              ><td class="cmp-leader">Static binary</td><td
                >877 KB x86_64 &middot; 801 KB aarch64</td
              ></tr
            >
            <tr
              ><td class="cmp-leader">Tests</td><td
                >595 passing &middot; 0 leaks &middot; 0 warnings</td
              ></tr
            >
            <tr><td class="cmp-leader">Parse throughput</td><td>5.96M lines/sec</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="cmp-leader">Ban latency</td><td>365 ns p50 &middot; 932 ns p99</td></tr>
            <tr
              ><td class="cmp-leader">Filters shipped</td><td
                >15 built-in &middot; sshd, nginx, apache, mail, db, more</td
              ></tr
            >
            <tr
              ><td class="cmp-leader">Honeypot</td><td
                >Lightsail &middot; 2+ day real-traffic soak</td
              ></tr
            >
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <div class="table-col">
        <div class="eyebrow"><span class="dot"></span>Tech stack</div>
        <h2 class="table-head">From engine to edge.</h2>
        <table class="stat-table">
          <tbody>
            <tr
              ><td class="cmp-leader">Engine</td><td
                >Zig 0.14.1 &middot; static musl &middot; zero runtime deps</td
              ></tr
            >
            <tr
              ><td class="cmp-leader">Event loop</td><td
                >io_uring / epoll &middot; timerfd &middot; signalfd</td
              ></tr
            >
            <tr
              ><td class="cmp-leader">Parser</td><td
                >Comptime-specialized &middot; no runtime regex</td
              ></tr
            >
            <tr
              ><td class="cmp-leader">Firewall</td><td
                >nftables via netlink &middot; ipset &middot; iptables</td
              ></tr
            >
            <tr
              ><td class="cmp-leader">Web</td><td
                >Astro 6 &middot; HTML + CSS &middot; Cloudflare Workers</td
              ></tr
            >
            <tr
              ><td class="cmp-leader">Infra</td><td
                >AWS Lightsail &middot; Cloudflare Tunnel (outbound-only)</td
              ></tr
            >
            <tr><td class="cmp-leader">CI/CD</td><td>GitHub Actions &middot; SHA-pinned Zig</td></tr
            >
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- thanks ────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <div class="thanks-head">
      <div class="eyebrow"><span class="dot"></span>Thanks</div>
      <h2 class="table-head">Credit where it's due.</h2>
    </div>

    <section class="row row-thanks" aria-label="Thanks">
      <article class="card card-thanks">
        <p class="card-label">The host</p>
        <h3 class="thanks-name">Vibe Rubin &amp; the judges</h3>
        <p>
          Vibe Rubin runs <a href="https://reddit.com/r/vibecoding" rel="noopener">r/vibecoding</a>
          and the Discord, thousands of members deep, where building in public is the norm. That steady
          community work is what makes events like this possible. Thanks also to Anything.com and VibesOS
          for sponsoring, and to the judges for putting their time into reviewing every submission.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="card card-thanks">
        <p class="card-label">The lineage</p>
        <h3 class="thanks-name">fail2ban</h3>
        <p>
          Twenty years of service protecting the open internet. fail2ban set the vocabulary: <code
            >jail.conf</code
          >, the filter patterns, the operator language that lets someone pick fail2zig up on day
          one. This submission is a modern implementation of an idea that lineage already proved.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="card card-thanks">
        <p class="card-label">The signal</p>
        <h3 class="thanks-name">Alan</h3>
        <p class="quote-line">&ldquo;Stay in your lane.&rdquo;</p>
        <p>
          Alan's always telling me this. The lane being security engineering, not the side quests.
          The hard problems were already under my nose. This submission is me finally listening.
        </p>
        <p class="thanks-sign">Thanks brother!</p>
      </article>
    </section>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .vibejam-wrap {
    max-width: 1280px;
    margin: 40px auto 120px;
    padding: 0 32px;
  }

  /* ── hero · the contest ─────────────────────────────────── */

  .hero {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 0.9fr) minmax(0, 1.1fr);
    gap: 48px;
    align-items: stretch;
    margin-bottom: 96px;
  }

  .hero-poster {
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    display: block;
  }
  .hero-poster img {
    display: block;
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    background: var(--bg-elev);
  }

  .hero-meta {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    justify-content: center;
    gap: 0;
  }
  .hero-kicker {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    color: var(--fg-faint);
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin: 0 0 14px;
  }
  .hero-title {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 56px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    color: var(--fg);
    line-height: 1;
    margin: 0 0 14px;
  }
  .hero-theme {
    font-family: var(--sans);
    font-size: 20px;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--accent);
    margin: 0 0 32px;
    line-height: 1.3;
    max-width: 32ch;
  }

  .hero-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    column-gap: 24px;
    row-gap: 18px;
    margin: 0 0 32px;
    padding: 20px 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--line-soft);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line-soft);
  }
  .hero-grid > div {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 4px;
  }
  .hero-grid dt {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 10.5px;
    color: var(--fg-faint);
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin: 0;
  }
  .hero-grid dd {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 13.5px;
    color: var(--fg);
    margin: 0;
    line-height: 1.35;
  }
  .hero-grid dd .sep {
    color: var(--fg-faint);
    margin: 0 2px;
  }
  .hero-grid dd a {
    color: var(--accent);
    text-decoration: none;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--accent-ghost);
  }
  .hero-grid dd a:hover {
    border-bottom-color: var(--accent);
  }

  .hero-intro {
    font-family: var(--sans);
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--fg-body);
    margin: 0 0 24px;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }
  .hero-intro strong {
    color: var(--fg);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  @media (max-width: 920px) {
    .hero {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 32px;
    }
    .hero-poster {
      max-width: 480px;
      margin: 0 auto;
    }
    .hero-title {
      font-size: 44px;
    }
    .hero-theme {
      font-size: 18px;
    }
  }
  @media (max-width: 520px) {
    .hero-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      row-gap: 14px;
    }
    .hero-title {
      font-size: 36px;
    }
    .hero-intro {
      white-space: normal;
    }
  }

  /* ── sections ─────────────────────────────────── */

  .section {
    margin: 80px 0;
  }
  .section h2 {
    font-size: 28px;
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    margin: 0 0 8px;
    color: var(--fg);
  }
  .section h3 {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--fg-dim);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    margin: 36px 0 14px;
  }
  .section p {
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--fg-body);
    max-width: 64ch;
    margin: 0 0 18px;
  }
  .section em {
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--fg);
  }
  .section code {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 0.9em;
    background: var(--bg-elev);
    padding: 1px 6px;
    border: 1px solid var(--line-soft);
  }
  .section-lede {
    font-family: var(--mono) !important;
    font-size: 12.5px !important;
    color: var(--fg-faint) !important;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em !important;
    text-transform: uppercase !important;
    margin: 0 0 24px !important;
  }

  /* ── theme · solution cards ─────────────────────────────── */

  .row {
    margin: 0 0 48px;
  }
  .row-story {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 20px;
    align-items: stretch;
  }

  .card {
    position: relative;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    background: var(--bg-elev);
    padding: 28px 32px 32px;
    min-width: 0;
  }
  /* Corner tick — matches install-block + threat-model diagram pattern. */
  .card::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    top: 0;
    left: 0;
    width: 18px;
    height: 2px;
    background: var(--accent);
  }
  .card::after {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    top: 0;
    left: 0;
    width: 2px;
    height: 18px;
    background: var(--accent);
  }
  .card-label {
    font-family: var(--mono) !important;
    font-size: 10.5px !important;
    letter-spacing: 0.14em !important;
    text-transform: uppercase !important;
    color: var(--fg-faint) !important;
    margin: 0 0 14px !important;
    max-width: none !important;
  }
  .card-solution .card-label,
  .card-theme .card-label {
    color: var(--accent) !important;
  }
  .card-head {
    font-family: var(--sans);
    font-size: 26px;
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    color: var(--fg);
    line-height: 1.2;
    margin: 0 0 18px;
  }
  .card > p {
    font-family: var(--sans) !important;
    font-size: 15px !important;
    line-height: 1.7 !important;
    color: var(--fg-body) !important;
    margin: 0 0 14px !important;
    max-width: none !important;
  }
  .card > p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0 !important;
  }
  .card em {
    color: var(--fg);
    font-style: italic;
  }
  .card strong {
    color: var(--fg);
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  .card code {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 0.9em;
    background: var(--bg);
    padding: 1px 6px;
    border: 1px solid var(--line-soft);
  }
  .card-close {
    margin-top: auto !important;
    padding-top: 14px;
    border-top: 1px dashed var(--line-soft);
  }

  .pull-under {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 13px;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: var(--accent);
    text-align: center;
    margin: 24px 0 96px;
    padding: 12px 16px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  @media (max-width: 820px) {
    .row-story {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
    .card {
      padding: 24px 22px 26px;
    }
    .card-head {
      font-size: 22px;
    }
  }

  /* ── what shipped + tech stack tables ─────────────────────── */
  /* Pattern mirrors the homepage .cmp-table: mono 13px, strong  */
  /* line separators between rows, 140px leader column.         */

  .row-tables {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 48px;
    margin: 0 0 96px;
  }
  .table-col {
    min-width: 0;
  }
  .table-col .eyebrow {
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }
  .table-head {
    font-family: var(--sans);
    font-size: 28px;
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    color: var(--fg);
    line-height: 1.15;
    margin: 0 0 20px;
  }
  .stat-table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 13px;
  }
  .stat-table td {
    text-align: left;
    padding: 14px 16px;
    vertical-align: top;
    color: var(--fg-body);
  }
  .stat-table tr {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--line-strong);
  }
  .stat-table tr:first-child {
    border-top: none;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line-strong);
  }
  .stat-table tr:last-child {
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line-strong);
  }
  .stat-table .cmp-leader {
    color: var(--fg);
    font-weight: 600;
    width: 170px;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }
  @media (max-width: 820px) {
    .row-tables {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 56px;
    }
  }

  /* ── thanks ─────────────────────────────────── */

  .thanks-head {
    margin: 0 0 24px;
  }
  .thanks-head .eyebrow {
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }

  .row-thanks {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 20px;
    margin: 0 0 96px;
  }
  .card-thanks {
    padding: 22px 24px 26px;
  }
  /* Thanks cards: no corner tick — use a bottom gold line instead. */
  .card-thanks::before {
    display: none;
  }
  .card-thanks::after {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    bottom: -1px;
    left: 0;
    right: 0;
    top: auto;
    width: auto;
    height: 2px;
    background: var(--accent);
  }
  .thanks-name {
    font-family: var(--sans);
    font-size: 18px;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--fg);
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    line-height: 1.2;
    margin: 0 0 14px;
  }
  .card-thanks p {
    font-family: var(--sans) !important;
    font-size: 14.5px !important;
    line-height: 1.65 !important;
    color: var(--fg-body) !important;
    margin: 0 0 12px !important;
  }
  .card-thanks p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0 !important;
  }
  .card-thanks em {
    color: var(--fg);
    font-style: italic;
  }
  .card-thanks code {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 0.9em;
    background: var(--bg);
    padding: 1px 6px;
    border: 1px solid var(--line-soft);
  }
  .quote-line {
    font-family: var(--mono) !important;
    font-size: 17px !important;
    color: var(--accent) !important;
    font-style: normal !important;
    letter-spacing: -0.005em !important;
    margin: 0 0 16px !important;
    padding: 10px 14px !important;
    border-left: 2px solid var(--accent-dim);
    background: var(--bg);
  }
  .thanks-sign {
    font-family: var(--mono) !important;
    font-size: 14px !important;
    color: var(--accent) !important;
    font-weight: 500 !important;
    margin-top: 14px !important;
    margin-bottom: 0 !important;
  }

  @media (max-width: 820px) {
    .row-thanks {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
